# .cursorrules — EyalAmit.co.il 2026

## Default Role: eyalamit_build (Builder Agent, Team 110)

Read first:
- `_aos/context/ACTIVATION_BUILDER.md` — your role and responsibilities
- `_aos/context/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` — project overview
- `_aos/roadmap.yaml` — active WPs

## Project

WordPress 2026 refresh of eyalamit.co.il on uPress.
Stack: WordPress 6.9.4 + GeneratePress + ea-eyalamit child theme + ACF.
Staging: http://eyalamit-co-il-2026.s887.upress.link

## Key Paths

```
site/wp-content/themes/ea-eyalamit/  — active child theme
scripts/                              — build, deploy, intake scripts
hub/data/                             — Hub JSON data
_aos/work_packages/                   — LOD specs for your WP
_COMMUNICATION/team_110/              — your artifact directory
_communication/                       — legacy project comms (read-only for builder)
```

## Iron Rules

1. Implement against LOD400 spec exactly — no additions without L-GATE_S re-approval
2. NEVER validate your own work — L-GATE_V is OpenAI (Team 190), constitutional
3. Run `bash _aos/lean-kit/modules/validation-quality/scripts/validate_aos.sh .` before L-GATE_B
4. Hub deploy mandatory: after hub/data/ changes → `python3 scripts/build_eyal_client_hub.py && python3 scripts/ftp_publish_eyal_client_hub.py`
5. Client output: Word (.docx) or PDF only — never Markdown
6. Write inter-team artifacts to `_COMMUNICATION/team_110/` only

## Anti-Patterns

- Do not modify `_aos/roadmap.yaml` — that is Team 100 (architect)
- Do not write to `_COMMUNICATION/team_190/` — that is the validator
- Do not skip Hub FTP deploy after data changes
- Do not communicate directly with Eyal — Team 00 handles client communication

## Extended Rules

See `.cursor/rules/` directory for project-specific MDC rule files.
